                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/884: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-02T11:00:00+03:25"
                            >November 2, 1943—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 3—4:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1039. My 1037.<note n="64" xml:id="d579fn64">Dated November 1, <ref
                            target="#pg_551">p. 551</ref>.</note> Prime Minister has requested
                    Millspaugh to postpone for one week the date on which his Mission will cease
                    work if income tax measure is not passed by the Majlis. Millspaugh has acceded
                    both because he does not wish to be intransigent and because he realizes that it
                    is not reasonable to expect the Majlis to pass such an important measure in one
                    session. He will stress in his reply to Prime Minister that Majlis failed to
                    take advantage of the 2 weeks which have elapsed since he presented his
                    resignation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
